{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review final triage (run 3: PASS, 0 blocking, 20 advisory — attestation over this material stands; this comment is the disposition record, deliberately non-material to preserve it). Pattern across runs 1-3: each round surfaced one level deeper; run-3 findings are child-story/ADR/test depth. DISPOSITION — FOLD INTO CHILD STORIES AT DECOMPOSITION (assigned): S2 story — assemble_merge_change_context signature must take the merge-path file list as an explicit input alongside auto_merge_diff + mergelist (fe192771, the round's top finding); cap-placement precision — MERGELIST_MAX_COMMITS is a count pre-cap, DIFF_CHAR_CAP governs the combined string, diff section truncated last (f95ed0c3); extend tests/unit _FakeGerrit with the four new client methods (f0f74d65); sequential REST fan-out latency budget + note (fc2fb799); observability.sh reason-dimension mechanics + the aws_cloudwatch_metric_alarm terraform resource, modelled on monitoring_s4b.tf (fe83fa83/f707a514/f487d44b/ff3c6696). S1 story — feature-branch-drivers membership policy constraints: initial members = repo admins + named operating agents, changes via admin-approved setup-project.sh edit (f8e6233f); back-out wording correction: 'no label/gate changes REQUIRED' — the copyCondition addition is inert absent merge changes (MERGE_FIRST_PARENT_UPDATE cannot match a non-merge patchset) and may be left or reverted (f51eb171/f90d5449). S3 story — verify checkout-gerrit-change-action fetches a merge refspec correctly; already the S3/S5 run-log done-definition (f6a211e0). JUSTIFIED, no action: g2p 'determine whether' cannot be resolved before 1fa8 ships g2p — the epic's stated planning horizon; S3 converts expectation to verified statement (f67e5550, standing from runs 1-2); 1fa8-deliverables-do-not-exist is the epic's explicit, user-directed assumption (f4b0eba6); local-git-diff alternative to REST fan-out rejected — Gerrit's REST auto-merge is the CANONICAL conflict-resolution base; recomputing locally reintroduces content-comparison divergence risk, the exact R4 fragility class this design eliminates (f32ad7cc); no feature-flag/canary for the merge path — acceptable: absent the new path a merge change fail-closes to -1 TODAY (409 guard), so worst-case regression equals current behavior, and back-out is redeploy-prior-image (f5d73737); pushMerge on a public-reachable Gerrit — bounded by the named narrow group + both label gates remain the enforcement point, recorded in the ADR (f1cabe96); DET compound-criteria — house epic style, standing justification (f607dd45)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782963490415358001,"uuid":"386378c9-77dc-45f4-8fb1-d7c58211ddd8"}